#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/exponent_calculator.html:101
msgid ""
"Review the calculated result, scientific notation, and detailed explanation"
msgstr ""
"Examinez le résultat calculé, la notation scientifique et l'explication "
"détaillée"

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/exponent_calculator.html:114
msgid "What is an exponent?"
msgstr "Qu'est-ce qu'un exposant ?"

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/exponent_calculator.html:117
msgid ""
"An exponent (or power) indicates how many times a number (base) is "
"multiplied by itself. For example, 2³ means 2 × 2 × 2 = 8."
msgstr ""
"Un exposant (ou puissance) indique combien de fois un nombre (base) est "
"multiplié par lui-même. Par exemple, 2³ signifie 2 × 2 × 2 = 8."

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/exponent_calculator.html:122
msgid "What is a negative exponent?"
msgstr "Qu'est-ce qu'un exposant négatif ?"

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/exponent_calculator.html:125
msgid ""
"A negative exponent means taking the reciprocal. For example, 2⁻³ = 1/(2³) ="
" 1/8 = 0.125."
msgstr ""
"Un exposant négatif signifie prendre l’inverse. Par exemple, 2⁻³ = 1/(2³) = "
"1/8 = 0,125."

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/exponent_calculator.html:130
msgid "What is a fractional exponent?"
msgstr "Qu'est-ce qu'un exposant fractionnaire ?"

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/exponent_calculator.html:133
msgid ""
"A fractional exponent represents a root. For example, 8^(1/3) = ∛8 = 2, "
"which is the cube root of 8."
msgstr ""
"Un exposant fractionnaire représente une racine. Par exemple, 8^(1/3) = ∛8 ="
" 2, qui est la racine cubique de 8."

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/exponent_calculator.html:138
msgid "What is the square root?"
msgstr "Quelle est la racine carrée ?"

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/exponent_calculator.html:141
msgid ""
"The square root of a number is a value that, when multiplied by itself, "
"gives the original number. For example, √16 = 4 because 4 × 4 = 16."
msgstr ""
"La racine carrée d’un nombre est une valeur qui, multipliée par elle-même, "
"donne le nombre d’origine. Par exemple, √16 = 4 car 4 × 4 = 16."

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/exponent_calculator.html:146
msgid "Can I calculate roots of negative numbers?"
msgstr "Puis-je calculer les racines de nombres négatifs ?"

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/exponent_calculator.html:149
msgid ""
"Odd roots (like cube root) of negative numbers are real numbers. Even roots "
"(like square root) of negative numbers are not real numbers (they are "
"complex)."
msgstr ""
"Les racines impaires (comme la racine cubique) des nombres négatifs sont des"
" nombres réels. Même les racines (comme la racine carrée) des nombres "
"négatifs ne sont pas des nombres réels (elles sont complexes)."

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/exponent_calculator.html:172
msgid ""
"Calculate exponents, powers, square roots, cube roots, and nth roots. "
"Supports positive, negative, and fractional exponents."
msgstr ""
"Calculez les exposants, les puissances, les racines carrées, les racines "
"cubiques et les racines nièmes. Prend en charge les exposants positifs, "
"négatifs et fractionnaires."

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/exponent_calculator.html:200
#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/exponent_calculator.html:222
msgid "Exponent"
msgstr "Exposant"

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/exponent_calculator.html:203
msgid "Root"
msgstr "Racine"

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/exponent_calculator.html:222
msgid "power"
msgstr "pouvoir"

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/exponent_calculator.html:227
msgid "Can be positive, negative, or fractional"
msgstr "Peut être positif, négatif ou fractionnaire"

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/exponent_calculator.html:244
#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/root_calculator.html:88
msgid "Root Index"
msgstr "Index racine"

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/exponent_calculator.html:244
msgid "n for nth root"
msgstr "n pour la nième racine"

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/exponent_calculator.html:249
msgid "2 = square root, 3 = cube root, etc."
msgstr "2 = racine carrée, 3 = racine cubique, etc."

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/exponent_calculator.html:260
msgid "Calculate exponent or root"
msgstr "Calculer l'exposant ou la racine"

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/exponent_calculator.html:308
msgid ""
"Enter base and exponent to calculate powers, or base and root index to "
"calculate roots."
msgstr ""
"Entrez la base et l'exposant pour calculer les puissances, ou la base et "
"l'indice racine pour calculer les racines."

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/exponent_calculator.html:365
msgid "What is an Exponent Calculator?"
msgstr "Qu'est-ce qu'un calculateur d'exposant ?"

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/exponent_calculator.html:367
msgid ""
"An exponent calculator computes the result of raising a base number to a "
"power (exponent). It also calculates roots, which are the inverse operation "
"of exponentiation."
msgstr ""
"Un calculateur d'exposant calcule le résultat de l'élévation d'un nombre de "
"base à une puissance (exposant). Il calcule également les racines, qui sont "
"l'opération inverse de l'exponentiation."

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/exponent_calculator.html:370
msgid ""
"This calculator supports positive, negative, and fractional exponents, as "
"well as various types of roots including square roots, cube roots, and nth "
"roots."
msgstr ""
"Cette calculatrice prend en charge les exposants positifs, négatifs et "
"fractionnaires, ainsi que divers types de racines, notamment les racines "
"carrées, les racines cubiques et les racines nièmes."

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/exponent_calculator.html:378
msgid "Select calculation type: Exponent (power) or Root"
msgstr "Sélectionnez le type de calcul : Exposant (puissance) ou Racine"

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/exponent_calculator.html:379
msgid ""
"For exponent: Enter base and exponent (can be positive, negative, or "
"fractional)"
msgstr ""
"Pour l'exposant : saisissez la base et l'exposant (ils peuvent être "
"positifs, négatifs ou fractionnaires)"

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/exponent_calculator.html:380
msgid ""
"For root: Enter base and root index (2 for square root, 3 for cube root, "
"etc.)"
msgstr ""
"Pour racine : saisissez la base et l'index racine (2 pour racine carrée, 3 "
"pour racine cubique, etc.)"

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/exponent_calculator.html:381
msgid "Click Calculate to get the result with step-by-step solution"
msgstr ""
"Cliquez sur Calculer pour obtenir le résultat avec une solution étape par "
"étape"

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/exponent_calculator.html:382
msgid ""
"Review the result, scientific notation, visualization, and detailed "
"explanation"
msgstr ""
"Examinez le résultat, la notation scientifique, la visualisation et "
"l'explication détaillée"

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/exponent_calculator.html:388
msgid "Understanding Exponents and Roots"
msgstr "Comprendre les exposants et les racines"

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/exponent_calculator.html:391
msgid "Positive Exponents"
msgstr "Exposants positifs"

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/exponent_calculator.html:393
msgid ""
"A positive exponent means multiplying the base by itself that many times. "
"Example: 2³ = 2 × 2 × 2 = 8."
msgstr ""
"Un exposant positif signifie multiplier la base par elle-même autant de "
"fois. Exemple : 2³ = 2 × 2 × 2 = 8."

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/exponent_calculator.html:397
msgid "Negative Exponents"
msgstr "Exposants négatifs"

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/exponent_calculator.html:399
msgid ""
"A negative exponent means taking the reciprocal. Example: 2⁻³ = 1/(2³) = 1/8"
" = 0.125."
msgstr ""
"Un exposant négatif signifie prendre l’inverse. Exemple : 2⁻³ = 1/(2³) = 1/8"
" = 0,125."

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/exponent_calculator.html:403
msgid "Fractional Exponents"
msgstr "Exposants fractionnaires"

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/exponent_calculator.html:405
msgid ""
"A fractional exponent represents a root. Example: 8^(1/3) = ∛8 = 2 (cube "
"root of 8)."
msgstr ""
"Un exposant fractionnaire représente une racine. Exemple : 8^(1/3) = ∛8 = 2 "
"(racine cubique de 8)."

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/exponent_calculator.html:409
msgid "Roots"
msgstr "Racines"

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/exponent_calculator.html:411
msgid ""
"A root is the inverse of exponentiation. Square root (√) is the 2nd root, "
"cube root (∛) is the 3rd root, etc."
msgstr ""
"Une racine est l’inverse de l’exponentiation. La racine carrée (√) est la "
"2ème racine, la racine cubique (∛) est la 3ème racine, etc."

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/exponent_calculator.html:422
msgid "Example 1: Positive Exponent"
msgstr "Exemple 1 : exposant positif"

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/exponent_calculator.html:423
msgid "Base: 2, Exponent: 3"
msgstr "Base : 2, Exposant : 3"

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/exponent_calculator.html:424
msgid "Result: 2³ = 8"
msgstr "Résultat : 2³ = 8"

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/exponent_calculator.html:427
msgid "Example 2: Negative Exponent"
msgstr "Exemple 2 : exposant négatif"

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/exponent_calculator.html:428
msgid "Base: 2, Exponent: -3"
msgstr "Base : 2, Exposant : -3"

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/exponent_calculator.html:429
msgid "Result: 2⁻³ = 0.125"
msgstr "Résultat : 2⁻³ = 0,125"

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/exponent_calculator.html:432
msgid "Example 3: Square Root"
msgstr "Exemple 3 : Racine carrée"

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/exponent_calculator.html:433
msgid "Base: 16, Root Index: 2"
msgstr "Base : 16, indice racine : 2"

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/exponent_calculator.html:434
msgid "Result: √16 = 4"
msgstr "Résultat : √16 = 4"

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/exponent_calculator.html:437
msgid "Example 4: Cube Root"
msgstr "Exemple 4 : racine cubique"

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/exponent_calculator.html:438
msgid "Base: 8, Root Index: 3"
msgstr "Base : 8, indice racine : 3"

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/exponent_calculator.html:439
msgid "Result: ∛8 = 2"
msgstr "Résultat : ∛8 = 2"

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/exponent_calculator.html:452
msgid "Zero raised to a negative power is undefined."
msgstr "Zéro élevé à une puissance négative n’est pas défini."

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/exponent_calculator.html:458
msgid ""
"Even roots of negative numbers are not real numbers (they are complex)."
msgstr ""
"Même les racines des nombres négatifs ne sont pas des nombres réels (elles "
"sont complexes)."

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/exponent_calculator.html:464
msgid "Odd roots of negative numbers are real numbers (e.g., ∛(-8) = -2)."
msgstr ""
"Les racines impaires de nombres négatifs sont des nombres réels (par "
"exemple, ∛(-8) = -2)."

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/exponent_calculator.html:470
msgid ""
"Very large exponents may result in overflow (result too large to represent)."
msgstr ""
"Des exposants très grands peuvent entraîner un débordement (résultat trop "
"grand pour être représenté)."

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/exponent_calculator.html:710
msgid "Exponential Function Visualization"
msgstr "Visualisation des fonctions exponentielles"

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/exponent_calculator.html:721
msgid "Root Visualization"
msgstr "Visualisation racine"

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/factor_calculator.html:4
#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/factor_calculator.html:21
msgid "Factor Calculator - Find All Factors & Prime Factorization"
msgstr ""
"Calculateur de facteurs - Trouver tous les facteurs et factorisation "
